Functions not related to the domains or sets described above are demonstrated in this session. 

## Duplicate observations 

The function `expand2` generates duplicated observations of a dataset based on the row indexes.     

Let's try an example using `iris` dataset. We will duplicate the first 4 rows x 5 times.    

```{r expand2}
# head iris
head(iris)
# duplicate the first 4 rows.
iris_5 <- expand2(iris, 1:4, 5)
# check duplicated records
duplicates(iris_5)

# we can just keep our duplicates, not all records
iris_5new <- expand2(iris, 1:4, 5, original = FALSE)
# check duplication
duplicates(iris_5new)
```


